      {
        "id": 3925353,
        "name": "David Bueker",
        "username": "David_Bu3ker",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/david_bu3ker/{size}/319725_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-11-04T11:24:32.703Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I haven\u2019t had the 2017. That said, IMO aging Beaujolais is is not a \u201cshould\u201d rather more a how do you want them to show. I don\u2019t \u201cintentionally\u201d age Beaujolais. It just happens because I buy way too much wine overall. It\u2019s a rare time when I drink a Beaujolais with more than 3-4 years on it and think that it was demonstrably better than when it was young. Good Beaujolais holds up fine with 10+ years on it, but is it better? Not in my opinion.</p>",
